text:
Clean install of Centos. All dependencies were met.

Steps to reproduce:
rpmbuild -tb httpd.2.4.6.tar.bz

Error at the end is:

Checking for unpackaged file(s): /usr/lib/rpm/check-files /root/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/httpd-2.4.6-1.x86_64
error: Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found:
   /usr/lib64/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_wstunnel.so



Checked the release notes and it looks like this module (mod_proxy_wstunnel) was just added but did not make it in to the httpd.spec files option.

httpd.2.4.4 builds without errors
